---
import EventLayout from "../../components/EventLayout.astro";

const images = [
  { src: "/signal-i/1.jpg", alt: "SIGNAL I" },
  { src: "/signal-i/8.jpg", alt: "SIGNAL I" },
  { src: "/signal-i/12.jpg", alt: "SIGNAL I" },
  { src: "/signal-i/15.jpg", alt: "SIGNAL I" },
  { src: "/signal-i/20.jpg", alt: "SIGNAL I" },
];
---

<EventLayout
  title="SIGNAL I"
  date="June 5, 2025"
  location="Antwerp, Belgium"
  type="Meetup"
  description="The first SIGNAL meetup - 50 people, demos instead of slides, and conversations that make you want to rewrite your roadmap."
  images={images}
>
  <p>SIGNAL is North Star's flagship AI and Robotics meetup. Not a conference. A room for people who build with intelligence. Fifty people showed up for the first edition.</p>
  <p>Thomas Huybrechts from imec opened with a live animatronics demo - a social robotics parrot that turned the room into a mix of fascination and nervous laughter. The kind of demo you don't forget.</p>
  <p>Samuel Berton and Daria Matviichuk, winners of our first hackathon, followed with a talk on their project Bugify and how vibecoding is eating the software industry. Two builders who shipped something real, standing on stage weeks later explaining why it matters.</p>
  <p>The kind of evening where you walk in with one idea and leave with three.</p>
</EventLayout>
